7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Krisp and Podcastle share a solid foundation of core features including Speech To Text, Noise Removal. Where Krisp pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Real Time, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Podcastle uniquely offers Text To Speech and Voice Cloning and Podcast Editing and Custom Voices, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Krisp holds an overall score of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 9/10, while Podcastle scores 7/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Krisp offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $8/mo, compared to Podcastle's starting price of $11.99/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Krisp's free tier and Podcastle's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
